ing neither\nthe damage size nor the load is known in order to predict both simultaneously\nfrom incoming DI test points. In applying this framework, two forms of GPRMs\n(standard and variational heteroscedastic) are used in order to critically\nassess their performances with respect to the three test cases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Jun 2021 16:38:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-29"}
