e recent, intense burst, S12 was forming stars\nat a moderate rate of $\\sim 3{-}5~M_{\\odot}~\\mbox{yr}^{-1}$, typical of spiral\ngalaxies. However, the system also experienced an earlier burst approximately\n$1{-}3$ Gyr ago. While fairly uncertain, we estimate that the SFR during this\nearlier burst was $\\sim20{-}30~M_{\\odot}~\\mbox{yr}^{-1}$, similar to the\ncurrent SFR in the Antennae and NGC 3256.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Jun 2021 17:59:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-27"}
